OL,3,GNorth East
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA band of rain, occasionally
OL,6,Fheavy, will clear away southeastwards
OL,7,Ffirst thing. Brighter conditions with
OL,8,Fsunny spells soon follow but also
OL,9,Fisolated, possibly heavy showers. Any
OL,10,Fshowers tending to ease during the
OL,11,Fafternoon. Wind easing. Cool.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FSome sunny spells to start
OL,14,Fthe evening, but showers moving in
OL,15,Ffrom the northwest, occasionally heavy
OL,16,Fwith a low risk of thunder.
OL,17,
OL,18,CTuesday:FA mixture of sunny spells and
OL,19,Fblustery showers on Tuesday, with a
OL,20,Frisk of hail and thunder. Feeling cool
OL,21,Ffor the time of year.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
